trans-unit.source: The readObject method is responsible for reading from the stream and restoring the classes fields. trans-unit.source: The remaining SPI methods putSpi(String,String), removeSpi(String) and childSpi(String) have more complicated exception behavior. They are not specified to throw BackingStoreException, as they can generally obey their contracts even if the backing store is unavailable. This is true because they return no information and their effects are not required to become permanent until a subsequent call to Preferences.flush() or Preferences.sync(). Generally speaking, these SPI methods should not throw exceptions. In some implementations, there may be circumstances under which these calls cannot even enqueue the requested operation for later processing. Even under these circumstances it is generally better to simply ignore the invocation and return, rather than throwing an exception. Under these circumstances, however, subsequently invoking flush() or sync would not imply that all previous operations had successfully been made permanent.

Generally speaking, these SPI methods should not throw exceptions. In some implementations, there may be circumstances under which these calls cannot even enqueue the requested operation for later processing. Even under these circumstances it is generally better to simply ignore the invocation and return, rather than throwing an exception. Under these circumstances, however, all subsequent invocations of flush() and sync should return false, as returning true would imply that all previous operations had successfully been made permanent.
trans-unit.target: Los métodos SPI restantes putSpi(String,String) , removeSpi(String) y childSpi(String) tienen un comportamiento de excepción más complicado. No están especificados para lanzar BackingStoreException , ya que generalmente pueden obedecer sus contratos incluso si la tienda de respaldo no está disponible. Esto es cierto porque no devuelven información y no es necesario que sus efectos se vuelvan permanentes hasta una llamada posterior a Preferences.flush() o Preferences.sync() . En términos generales, estos métodos SPI no deberían generar excepciones. En algunas implementaciones, puede haber circunstancias en las que estas llamadas ni siquiera pueden poner en cola la operación solicitada para su procesamiento posterior. Incluso en estas circunstancias, generalmente es mejor simplemente ignorar la invocación y el retorno, en lugar de lanzar una excepción. Sin embargo, en estas circunstancias, todas las invocaciones posteriores de flush() y sync deben devolver false , ya que devolver true implicaría que todas las operaciones anteriores se habían hecho permanentes con éxito.

trans-unit.source: The reverberation parameters provided by ReverbType consist of the delay time and intensity of early reflections, the delay time and intensity of late reflections, and an overall decay time. Early reflections are the initial individual low-order reflections of the direct signal off the surfaces in the room. The late Reflections are the dense, high-order reflections that characterize the room's reverberation. The delay times for the start of these two reflection types give the listener a sense of the overall size and complexity of the room's shape and contents. The larger the room, the longer the reflection delay times. The early and late reflections' intensities define the gain (in decibels) of the reflected signals as compared to the direct signal. These intensities give the listener an impression of the absorptive nature of the surfaces and objects in the room. The decay time defines how long the reverberation takes to exponentially decay until it is no longer perceptible ("effective zero"). The larger and less absorbent the surfaces, the longer the decay time.
trans-unit.target: Los parámetros de reverberación proporcionados por ReverbType consisten en el tiempo de retardo y la intensidad de las reflexiones tempranas, el tiempo de retardo y la intensidad de las reflexiones tardías y un tiempo de caída general. Los primeros reflejos son los reflejos individuales iniciales de bajo orden de la señal directa de las superficies de la habitación. Los reflejos tardíos son los reflejos densos y de alto orden que caracterizan la reverberación de la habitación. Los tiempos de retardo para el inicio de estos dos tipos de reflexión le dan al oyente una idea del tamaño general y la complejidad de la forma y el contenido de la sala. Cuanto más grande sea la habitación, mayores serán los tiempos de retardo de la reflexión. Las intensidades de las reflexiones tempranas y tardías definen la ganancia (en decibelios) de las señales reflejadas en comparación con la señal directa. Estas intensidades dan al oyente una impresión de la naturaleza absorbente de las superficies y objetos de la habitación.El tiempo de caída define cuánto tiempo tarda la reverberación en decaer exponencialmente hasta que ya no es perceptible ("cero efectivo"). Cuanto más grandes y menos absorbentes sean las superficies, mayor será el tiempo de descomposición.

The selection state of a JList is managed by another separate model, an instance of ListSelectionModel. JList is initialized with a selection model on construction, and also contains methods to query or set this selection model. Additionally, JList provides convenient methods for easily managing the selection. These methods, such as setSelectedIndex and getSelectedValue, are cover methods that take care of the details of interacting with the selection model. By default, JList's selection model is configured to allow any combination of items to be selected at a time; selection mode MULTIPLE_INTERVAL_SELECTION. The selection mode can be changed on the selection model directly, or via JList's cover method. Responsibility for updating the selection model in response to user gestures lies with the list's ListUI.

The size of the frame includes any area designated for the border. The dimensions of the border area may be obtained using the getInsets method, however, since these dimensions are platform-dependent, a valid insets value cannot be obtained until the frame is made displayable by either calling pack or show. Since the border area is included in the overall size of the frame, the border effectively obscures a portion of the frame, constraining the area available for rendering and/or displaying subcomponents to the rectangle which has an upper-left corner location of (insets.left, insets.top), and has a size of width - (insets.left + insets.right) by height - (insets.top + insets.bottom).
